'''Cataplexy''' is a medical condition. People who have cataplexy will sometimes see that some of their [[muscle]]s suddenly fail them. Cataplexy  often affects people who have [[narcolepsy]]. Narcolepsy is a disorder. People with narcolepsy tend to suddenly fall asleep. They cannot control when they fall asleep. Cataplexy is sometimes confused with [[epilepsy]], where a series of flashes or other stimuli cause superficially similar [[seizure]]s.

The term Cataplexy originates from the [[Greek language|Greek]] ''kata'', meaning down, and ''plexis'', meaning a stroke or seizure.


